# Manual API smoke tests — open in REST Client (VS Code) or run via curl.

### Create / re-fetch a custodial user wallet
POST http://localhost:3000/api/create-user
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lightningAddress": "alice@example.com",
  "username": "alice",
  "email": ""
}

### Wallet balance
GET http://localhost:3000/api/wallet-balance/alice@example.com

### Start today's quiz (5 personalised questions)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lightningAddress": "alice@example.com"
}

### Submit answers (1500 sats reward on a perfect 5/5)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lightningAddress": "alice@example.com",
  "score": 5,
  "total": 5
}

### Attempts log
GET http://localhost:3000/api/logs

### LNURL-auth: bootstrap a challenge (returns k1 + bech32 LNURL)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/lnurl/init

### LNURL-auth: poll challenge status (paste the k1 from /init above)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/lnurl/status?k1={{k1}}

### LNURL-auth: who am I (uses the session cookie set by /status)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me

### LNURL-auth: set the payout LN address after first login
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/payout-address
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lightning_address": "alice@example.com"
}

### LNURL-auth: log out
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/logout

### Headless LNURL-auth signing (run with `node` from quiz/app/):
###   node -e 'const s = require("@noble/secp256k1"); const c = require("crypto"); \
###     s.utils.hmacSha256Sync = (k, ...m) => { const h = c.createHmac("sha256", Buffer.from(k)); \
###     m.forEach(b => h.update(Buffer.from(b))); return h.digest(); }; \
###     const k1 = process.argv[1]; const priv = s.utils.randomPrivateKey(); \
###     const pub = s.getPublicKey(priv, true); const sig = s.signSync(Buffer.from(k1, "hex"), priv); \
###     console.log("sig=" + Buffer.from(sig).toString("hex") + " key=" + Buffer.from(pub).toString("hex"));' <K1_HEX>
###
### Then hit the callback the wallet would hit:
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/lnurl/callback?tag=login&k1={{k1}}&sig={{sig}}&key={{key}}
